##  Installation Guide

### Prerequisites
- Node.js (v14 or higher)
- MongoDB (local or Atlas)
- Git
- Postman (for API testing)

### Step 1: Clone the Repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/umuahia-youth-platform.git
cd umuahia-youth-platform
Step 2: Install Dependencies
bash
# Install root dependencies
npm install

# Install backend dependencies
cd backend
npm install

# Install frontend dependencies
cd ../frontend
npm install
Step 3: Set Up Environment Variables
Backend (.env file in /backend directory):

env
PORT=5000
MONGODB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/umuahia-youth
JWT_SECRET=your-super-secret-jwt-key-change-this-in-production
Frontend (.env file in /frontend directory):

env
REACT_APP_API_URL=http://localhost:5000
Step 4: Create Uploads Directory
bash
cd backend
mkdir uploads
🚀 Running the Application
Development Mode
bash
# From the root directory
npm run dev
This will start both backend (port 5000) and frontend (port 3000) concurrently.

Production Build
bash
# Build frontend
cd frontend
npm run build

# Serve with Node.js
cd ../backend
npm start
📚 API Documentation
Base URL
text
http://localhost:5000/api
Authentication Endpoints
Method	Endpoint	Description	Auth
POST	/auth/register	Register new user	Public
POST	/auth/login	User login	Public
Youth Endpoints
Method	Endpoint	Description	Auth
GET	/youth	Get all youth	Public
GET	/youth/stats	Get youth statistics	Public
GET	/youth/:id	Get single youth	Public
Posts Endpoints
Method	Endpoint	Description	Auth
GET	/posts	Get all posts	Public
POST	/posts	Create post	Admin
GET	/posts/announcements	Get announcements	Public
POST	/posts/announcements	Create announcement	Admin
Admin Endpoints
Method	Endpoint	Description	Auth
GET	/admin/users	Get all users	Admin
GET	/admin/stats	Get admin stats	Admin
DELETE	/admin/users/:id	Delete user	Admin
🔍 Testing with Postman
Import Collection
Open Postman

Click "Import" → "Raw Text"

Paste the collection JSON from the testing guide

Set environment variable: base_url = http://localhost:5000/api

Test Data
Register a user:

json
{
  "fullName": "Chinedu Okeke",
  "email": "chinedu.okeke@example.com",
  "phone": "08012345678",
  "dateOfBirth": "1998-03-20",
  "community": "Ibeku",
  "address": "15 Ibeku Road, Umuahia",
  "occupation": "Teacher",
  "password": "password123"
}
Create an announcement (Admin):

json
{
  "title": "NNPC Graduate Trainee Program",
  "description": "Apply for NNPC graduate trainee program 2024",
  "type": "Job",
  "link": "https://nnpc.gov.ng/careers"
}
Creating Admin User
After registering a user, make them admin in MongoDB:

javascript
// Connect to MongoDB
use umuahia-youth
db.users.updateOne(
  { email: "your-email@example.com" },
  { $set: { role: "admin" } }
)
🌐 Deployment Guide
Deploy to Render (Backend)
Push code to GitHub

Create new Web Service on Render

Connect repository

Set:

Build Command: npm install

Start Command: npm start

Environment Variables: Add all .env variables

Deploy to Vercel (Frontend)
Install Vercel CLI: npm i -g vercel

Run vercel in frontend directory

Follow prompts

Set environment variables in Vercel dashboard

Deploy to MongoDB Atlas
Create Atlas cluster

Get connection string

Update MONGODB_URI in environment variables

